You make plans for years and when you finally get around to making them happen, you have some of the best experiences of your life. My bestie @ngiannino joined me and our childhood friend @danchaparian on a west coast jaunt this past summer, hitting up some of the regions most beautiful spots. Road trips are just better with good friends!

Dad’s morning out. This was the last outdoor adventure for me before my daughter was born, and one of the last as @jbmccrar anticipated the birth of his daughter. Life moves in weird ways. I’ll never stop loving crisp morning air, stunning mountain peaks, spontaneous travel and, especially, deep powder turns. 

But I’ve also come to love the smell of my daughter’s head, her baby stretches and tiny hands, my toddler’s laugh and his nonsensical knock-knock jokes, even more. I’ve got a lifetime of outdoor adventures ahead of me, but I’m cherishing these quiet moments nonetheless. 

When you boil it down, everything is an adventure. 
@eddiebauer #eddiebauer #liveyouradventure #ebcontributor

Few experiences are more magnificent than watching the sunrise from 9,000 feet among the spires of the American Alps: @ncascadesnps . These are just a few of the dozens of scenes we filmed in support of the @wanatlparkfund to showcase just how much #ourbackyardrocks and help raise funds for Washington State’s three national parks. 

And a huge thank you to @lighthawk_org for their continued contributions to our parks by donating flights like these to gather aerial imagery—it wouldn’t be possible without them! #lighthawk

One of the best parts about Giving Tuesday is that you can celebrate it any day. If you love public lands and particularly our three magnificent National Parks here in Washington State, the @wanatlparkfund is a fantastic organization to support. Their fundraising efforts have made countless projects in our parks possible over the years and they continue to be a key partner in preserving and improving @olympic_nps , @ncascadesnps , and @mountrainiernps 

I hope you’ll join me in supporting them not just now but throughout the year. 

And as always, these aerial images wouldn’t be possible without the continued generosity of @lighthawk_org and their pilots who are as committed to the preservation of these wild places as anyone. Thank you!
